  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  18 years or older male and female cigarette smokers motivated and willing to stop
             smoking

          -  Female participants of child-bearing potential should use a medically acceptable means
             of birth control.

          -  Evidence of a personally signed and dated informed consent document indicating that
             the subject has been informed of all pertinent aspects of the study and consents to
             participate.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Unstable angina pectoris or myocardial infarction during the previous 3 months.

          -  Pregnancy, lactation or intended pregnancy (non-pregnancy will be verified by urine
             pregnancy test for female participants of child-bearing potential).

          -  Participation in other clinical trials within the previous three months and during
             study participation.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
